President Donald J. Trump spoke with Prime Minister Theresa May of the United Kingdom. They discussed the upcoming summit between the United States and North Korea, as well as the need for a comprehensive deal addressing Iran's destabilizing behavior in Yemen and Syria. The President also emphasized the importance of rebalancing trade with Europe and expressed hope for a Brexit deal that avoids increasing tensions on the Northern Ireland border. They also talked about their goals for the upcoming G7 Summit in Canada and the President's visit to the United Kingdom in July.